      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I'm not a doctor, but I can try to help. It's probably not a good idea to take extra-strength ibuprofen or oxy without consulting a medical professional, especially if you're not sure what's causing the pain. Taking high doses of ibuprofen can irritate the stomach and worsen cramps, and oxy can be habit-forming and mask underlying issues. Consider trying some ginger tea or peppermint oil to help soothe the stomach, and if the pain persists, you might want to try a warm bath or a heating pad to relax.",
